#NOTES
ðŸ”¤ PYTHON STRING METHODS CHART
ðŸ”¹ Case Conversion Methods
Method	Use	Example	Output
upper()	Convert to uppercase	"hello".upper()	"HELLO"
lower()	Convert to lowercase	"HELLO".lower()	"hello"
capitalize()	First letter capital	"python".capitalize()	"Python"
title()	Capitalize each word	"hello world".title()	"Hello World"
swapcase()	Swap case	"PyThOn".swapcase()	"pYtHoN"
ðŸ”¹ Space Handling Methods
Method	Use	Example	Output
strip()	Remove both sides space	" hi ".strip()	"hi"
lstrip()	Remove left space	" hi ".lstrip()	"hi "
rstrip()	Remove right space	" hi ".rstrip()	" hi"
ðŸ”¹ Search & Count Methods
Method	Use	Example	Output
find()	Find index	"hello".find("e")	1
index()	Find index (error if not found)	"hello".index("e")	1
count()	Count substring	"banana".count("a")	3
startswith()	Check start	"hello".startswith("h")	True
endswith()	Check end	"hello".endswith("o")	True
ðŸ”¹ Replace & Split Methods
Method	Use	Example	Output
replace(a,b)	Replace text	"hi".replace("h","H")	"Hi"
split()	Split string â†’ list	"a b c".split()	['a','b','c']
split(",")	Split by comma	"a,b,c".split(",")	['a','b','c']
join(list)	Join list â†’ string	" ".join(['hi','all'])	"hi all"
ðŸ”¹ Checking Methods (Boolean)
Method	Use	Example	Output
isupper()	All uppercase?	"HELLO".isupper()	True
islower()	All lowercase?	"hi".islower()	True
isdigit()	Only digits?	"123".isdigit()	True
isalpha()	Only letters?	"abc".isalpha()	True
isalnum()	Letters + digits	"a1".isalnum()	True
isspace()	Only spaces	" ".isspace()	True
ðŸ”¹ Formatting Methods
Method	Use	Example	Output
format()	Format string	"My age is {}".format(20)	"My age is 20"
center(w)	Center text	"hi".center(6)	" hi "
zfill(n)	Add zeros	"45".zfill(4)	"0045"
